inn1.comm: starts off right on a length close to off stump getting Taylor to defend off the front foot
gentle stuff on a length outside off stump, Taylor has a look at it, and decides to leave
128.4 kph, a bit of wobble in the air as this one straightens a shade but comfortably outside off for him to leave
he's had enough of a look, realised there is not much pace off the pitch, waited for this one to arrive and then crashed it past cover
shapes away, he is keeping it outside off stump, left alone again
the ball is coming very slowly off the surface, he shuffles across, and gets an inside edge away in front of mid on
wide and left alone outside the off stump
well, this deserved to be put away, three feet outside off, and short on top of that, Taylor rocked back and cut it fiercely past point, no one moved
bowls it fuller, but still wide outside off, he comes forward and tries to smash it away, but mistimes to mid off
that's the area, coming in with the angle on off stump, he carefully pats it away
tries to get forward to punch this one away past extra cover but cannot get the timing
gets him to come forward in picture-perfect forward defence as he bowls a length ball that comes in close to off stump
hangs the bat out at one outside off stump, opens the face and gets it past point, and wide of third man to get off the mark
gets forward and blocks this length delivery

the slip cordon go up in hope, the bowler has hands on his hips, he got front pad across on of stump, and wanted to flick it over fine leg, but got an inside edge on to pad that saved him, else he was right in front
pitching miles outside off stump, and then moving several inches away
closer to off this time, but still enough time and space ti leave it alone
on the stumps on a length, pushed away on the leg side
and one goes past the outside edge! pulls out this length ball outside off from nowhere, it holds the line and goes past his forward push
more compact forward defence from Taylor, no flourish, just a stride forward and a resolute block
this one takes off from a length, a bit two-paced this surface, he was already in the forward movement, and took it on the glove, fortunately there was no one close in at short leg
another one holds its line outside off stump, he was a bit tentative after taking the earlier one on the glove, belatedly tried to have a poke, and was beaten
now this one comes in, this is good stuff, but starting a bit far outside off to make him play
lunges forward in defence, and takes on the man running in from midwicket for a tight single
very full outside the off stump, he tries to squeeze it away, gets it down to third man
some bounce at 117.2 kph, hmm, extra lift from a length outside off stump, he lets it go
pushes out purposefully, and gets it wide of cover for a comfortable run
good away shape on this one, pitches on a length and then loops away, he leaves with a flourish after coming forward
looking to break free, fortunate that one did not crash in to the stumps, wanted to heave this one from outside off over midwicket, but got an inside edge on to pad as it kept a shade low
gets back to a short of a length ball and punches it to extra cover

this time he will get what he wants, this one wan angled in fuller on the stumps, and he used the angle neatly, flicking high in the air over midwicket, and the ball trickled in to the ropes to beat the man chasing it
128.3 kph homing in on the off stump, but he gets right behind the line and defends
pushed away off the front foot in to the off side, this is tight stuff from the Kenyans
133.7 kph this one cuts back in sharply from a length, and stays a bit low too, Regis had backed away for the cut, but he had no chance as it nipped back, this looks a pretty abrasive surface
this time he gets to the pitch of a fuller one and drives it wide of third man
walks two feet outside off stump, and blocks it away to point
pushes one away in front of point, and wants the run, Regis says 'no'
blocked confidently off the back foot
goes flailing at a widish one that moves away from him, and is nowhere to the line of the ball
comes forward and meets the length ball with a broad defensive bat

lovely drive, gets forward, covers for the away movement by staying slightly beside the line and opens the face to drive in the gap at cover, Nehemiah goes charging after the ball, but it has too much of a headstart
better line, on the stumps, defended on the leg side
misses the flick and it rolls away fine off the pads, David is quick to get to his left and cut off any attempts of a run
134.7 kph full delivery, Taylor has had enough of convention, swipes across the line, and gets enough on it to get it past the non-striker and down the ground
gets some width outside off, and goes hard at it, but gets it straight to third  man
good work by Mishra at point, it was cut hard and travelling fast, he dived to his right, got body behind ball, and stopped it cleanly
slower one, he comes out and threads the gap at cover, but Obanda goes flying horizontally to his left to cut off a certain boundary
shuffles and plays this one on the leg side
crashed off the front foot, but Mishra makes another diving save at point, Kenya have been good in the field
shuffles across and plays this one away on the leg side
bounces and thuds into the high part of the bat as he pushes forward
138.6 kph short of a length ball that he looks to turn away through square leg but takes it on the pads
already he is making some difference with his extra pace, getting one to hold its line outside off, and he uncertainly pushes at it and gets a thick edge to third man
stays on the back foot and guides a bouncing delivery to point

135.7 kph, and Nehemiah strikes in his first over, lovely delivery, very close to off stump, getting him to push forward at it, moves away off to take the outside edge, and David Obuya gleefully accepts the dolly
shuffles and pushes off the front foot in to the off side
drives off the front foot, mid off gets quickly to his left and fires in the throw
too full and angled in on leg stump, he works it away neatly and short midwicket had no chance once it got past him

Kenya have got the big one, Taylor departs to a nothing shot, this one was not on the pads, he still tries to flick it away, it was outside off stump, he did not get across and ended up scooping it in the air to mid on
left alone outside the off stump
tails on from a length outside off, he leaves again
hustles in and bowls a 137.6 kph length delivery that is wisely left alone outside off
gets behind the line of one that bounces extra around middle stump, two-paced nature coming through again, loops in the air on the leg side
he puts it lot off effort but it comes slowly off the pitch outside off stump, left alone
another one left alone outside the off stump
wide outside off stump, he lets it be
sticks to his guns outside off, and this time gets him to stab at it, but the lack of pace in the pitch means it falls short of second slip
and is right away dispatched through extra cover, very full outside off, got to the pitch, leaned in to the drive, and got it in the gap, then the outfield took over
they pinch a single as this one rolls away off the pads in front of midwicket
comes forward a long way, but ends up pushing outside the line to one that cuts back in, it is the off-cutter, but he is struck outside the line of off
whoa, Taibu zooms down the wicket, pushes one in front of the non-striker, and zips across for the run, mid on had no chance against the little man
pushes forward in resolute defence
gets back this time to push a length ball to the bowler

Tikolo goes for the review to one that nips in to strike Taibu on the pads, but that would have missed leg stump, Nehemiah was interested, umpire Dharmasena had already said not out, replays only confirm that
goes on his toes to guide one past point
shuffles and neatly works this one with the angle past midwicket, got lot of wood on that one, just pulled back inside the ropes
lifter outside off stump, come back in off the seam, left alone

Odoyo has a shy at the stumps, and misses, by a long way, Sibanda was almost at Taibu's end in his mad rush for the single, but Taibu sent him back, Odoyo dived at mid on and at the same moment fired in the throw, which is why it was about three feet wide of the stumps
pushed away in to the cover
walks down the track, and defends a length ball on the leg side
turned off the pads in front of square leg, Mishra runs forward from the deep midwicket boundary to field
this outfield is so quick, just seemed a push in the gap at cover, but it beat the fielder to the ropes, he even put in the dive, but to no avail
shuffles to work this one away on the leg side
this pitch is playing its tricks, this one didn't get up at all, fortunately for the batsman it was down the leg side, David Obuya had to do some work to stop it
again he walks down the track defend this one
played out from the crease on the leg side
driven off the front foot in to the covers
slaps a length ball to point
opens him up a bit, but he manages to push this length ball to mid off
pushed out towards mid on
stands tall, rides the bounce on this one outside off and punches it nicely to point
tries the bouncer this time, it goes way above the batsman's head
strays on the pads, he picks it down to fine leg
it's time for those singles down the ground as a tossed up ball it driven to long on
fired in quicker on off stump, pushed down the track
whipped away with the turn from outside off to deep midwicket
the innovator in Taibu quickly comes to the fore, goes down on a knee, lunges forward and helps a turning delivery past short third man with the reverse paddle
tries to do so again, but this one is around middle and he awkwardly dabs it away to short third man
turning in around leg stump, played out towards midwicket
short of a length ball doesn't get waist high, played from the crease behind point
good length delivery angling into Sibanda who gets behind the line and defends from the crease
another ball doesn't get up much, Sibanda defends on the back foot towards the off and calls for a quick single
Taibu takes one hand off the bat as he tries to pull, he was too early on the short and the ball lobbed up safely towards midwicket
played off the pads towards midwicket, fuller ball this time
short of a length, Sibanda goes back and works the ball off his hips through square leg
a touch shorter and Sibanda goes back in his crease and pulls to deep square
much shorter and Taibu pulls powerfully to the man on the square leg boundary
played off the back foot towards point
bowled with loop on leg stump, the batsman misses the glance and gets hit on the pad
flighted delivery which lands in the blockhole, the batsman digs it out
played back to the bowler from the crease
bowled on a tight length around off stump. Defended on the front foot
Taibu bottom edges the cut towards backward point and sets off
worked off the pads towards square leg where a fumble allows the run
pushed towards long on for a single
played off the pads towards midwicket
turned off the pads through square leg for a single
played back to the bowler from the crease
a bit of width outside off and the batsman moves back to cut through point
driven off the front foot towards cover
Sibanda steps out to take the ball on the full and drives towards Obuya's left. Obuya leaps and fields the ball with one hand.
strays down leg and Sibanda gets down on one knee and sweeps fine for four
he steps out to take the ball on the full once again and pulls powerfully to the fielder on the deep midwicket boundary

loud appeal for lbw as Sibanda pushes forward to defend and gets hit on the pad. Umpire Dharmasena says not out and Kenya want a review. Replays indicate it would have missed leg by a long way. Kenya have used both their reviews.
width offered outside off and Sibanda cuts deftly off the back foot. This outfield is so quick the ball speeds to the third-man boundary
Sibanda strides forward and defends on the off side
dabbed from the crease past the fielder at short fine leg
played off the back foot towards short fine leg
fuller length on middle and leg, flicked firmly off the front foot through midwicket where a mis-field on the boundary allows four. Shoddy work
cut off the back foot towards deep point
the length is a bit short, allowing Sibanda the space to punch off the back foot through cover
looped through the air and Taibu stays in his crease, takes it on the full and drives to long-off
short ball and Sibanda cuts hard off the back foot through point
very short once again, Taibu hits it back towards the bowler and Obuya makes a fine save towards his left
played towards point
defended on the off side
defended on the front foot towards midwicket
flicked off the pads towards deep midwicket
dabbed off the back foot towards point
flicked off the pads behind square
Taibu pulls the reverse sweep out of his bag and makes terrific contact, he plays that shot rather well
driven off the front foot towards long off
played back to the bowler
Taibu stays in his crease and nudges the ball off his pads through square
leg stump once again and Sibanda goes deep into his crease and flicks the ball through square
tossed up on off, Taibu strides and defends
cut off the back foot towards extra cover
that's rubbish, a long hop outside leg stump, Sibanda swivels and pulls towards the long-leg boundary
short again, punched off the back foot through extra cover
defended on the back foot
tossed up on off stump, the batsman moves forward and blocks
played towards deep midwicket
defended on the front foot towards the bowler
pushed off the back foot towards the bowler
Taibu moves back and works the ball towards square
Sibanda moves on the front foot and pushes towards the bowler
Sibanda gets down on one knee and sweeps powerfully towards deep square where Odhiambo slides and saves the boundary
played towards cover for a quick single
dabbed behind point for one more
short of a length, played towards point off the back foot
short of a length again, played from the crease towards the bowler
dabbed off the back foot towards third man
good length ball outside off, defended solidly off the front foot towards cover
short ball and Sibanda tries to pull but gets beaten, that ball didn't rise as much as Sibanda thought it would
the slower ball on middle stump, Sibanda moves forward and blocks
tossed up on off and middle, played back to the bowler
Taibu backs away towards leg, makes room, and cuts from just outside off through the gap at point, superbly timed and it races away on a fast outfield
Taibu moves back and plays the ball off his pads behind square
and again, Taibu makes room and slaps the ball from off stump through cover for four more, placed the ball in front of the fielder on the deep point boundary
nudged off the back foot towards square
shot! Sibanda reaches 50 by stepping out, getting to the pitch of the ball and lofting it with a wonderfully straight bat over the long-on boundary

Sibanda would have been run out had there been a direct hit! Taibu dabbed the ball towards cover point and took two steps forward. Sibanda charged for the single and was sent back very late. The fielder at cover point missed at the bowler's end with Sibanda in the middle of the pitch
short ball and Taibu lets it pass
that's extremely wide down leg side, the slower ball gone wrong
short of a length outside off, cut off the back foot towards third man
defended on the back foot towards the leg side
that's poor, with fine leg in the circle. Leg stump line at gentle pace, Sibanda glances the ball fine and helps himself to four easy runs
edged and that's just wide of the wicketkeeper. Sibanda was looking to cut a short of a length ball and ended up edging it to third man

a massive mix-up again and this time Sibanda is run out! Taibu pushed the ball towards cover point and took off down the pitch. He then decided he didn't want to run and backtracked into his crease while looking at the ball the whole time. He didn't see that his partner Sibanda had responded and was haring through for the single. The fielder at cover point ran to the non-striker's end with his arms raised in celebration and took off the bails.
beaten outside the off stump

huge appeal for lbw and Asoka de Silva raises the finger. Taibu wants a review. That ball pitched around off and angled sharply into the right-hander. Taibu missed the ball and was hit on the pad. Replays show it would have missed leg stump. Asoka gets another one wrong ...
similar ball but this time Taibu gets a stride in and punches towards the bowler
blasted through cover! Taibu gets on to the front foot and lashes a full ball with a fierce swing of his bat
Taibu tries to play the ball behind point but gets a bottom edge into the ground towards the keeper
pushed off the front foot towards point with an open face
defended on the leg side
pushed of the front foot towards cover
short ball down leg side and Ervine glances the ball off his pads past the fielder at short fine leg
defended on the front foot towards the leg side
Ervine pushes forward to defend and gets an edge that falls short of first slip and beats the fielder and runs to the third-man boundary
good length ball and straight, defended on the back foot towards the bowler
loud call on NO, after Taibu pushes the ball off the back foot towards point
Taibu gets to 50 with a cut that races to the backward point boundary, he brings up 3000 runs in ODIs as well.
the slower ball bowled wide outside off, Taibu moves forward and mis-times the drive
Taibu stays in his crease and defends a good length ball on the leg side
another slower ball on off and middle, defended on the front foot
Ervine moves forward, gets down on one knee and sweeps the ball with power towards deep square
worked off the pads from the crease towards square
defended on the front foot towards the bowler

that's lbw! Taibu attempts the reverse sweep and misses. The ball hits him rather straight on off and middle line. Umpire Dharmasena raises the finger quickly. Taibu wants a review, but it's futile. That would have hit the middle of middle. Start the car ...
pushes forward and defends on the leg side
stays back and pushes one away in to the off side
tossed up outside off from round the stumps, gets him to reach out and push towards covers
Tikolo produces the leading edge as he looks to clip it through midwicket, but it seemed to fall just short of Collins who dived forward
pished away on the leg side
almost a run out, Ervine came charging for the single as the ball was played to square leg, had to rush back from more than halfway down the pitch, the throw was side at Tikolo's end
played in the air, could have been dangerous, but it dropped short of midwicket
tight over from Tikolo ends, played away off the back foot
goes for the sweep to one that turns in from outside leg, but short fine leg makes good ground to his left to cut off the run
eases this one away down to long on for a single
poor bowling, this one is pushed down the leg side, turns further away from the batsman, keeps low too, in short, keeper had not much chance
comes down the track and pushes a fuller one down to long on
lovely delivery, that has turned so much, flighted outside leg, he tried to adjust from the turn and pushed forward around middle, the ball turned way past the off stump
this time he stays in the crease, does not commit early, and punches this one towards covers
gets one on the pads and works it away through square leg
pushes out this length delivery towards sweeper cover for an easy single
straightens a shade close to off stump, he comes out and blocks
looks to come forward in defence, it cuts back in from outside off stump, and he takes it on the body, that bounced too
more bounce for Ongondo, this one takes off from back of a length, and it hits him high on the defensive blade
pushed out to point this time off the back foot
does not commit forward fully and stabs at this length delivery to send it down to third man, again some disconcerting lift, even from a slightly fuller length
purposefully skips down the track and eases this one with the turn to long on
tossed up outside leg stump, and he takes it on the pad as he misses the sweep, bowler and keeper are interested, but it pitched way outside leg
defended in to the off side towards point
again down the leg side, he turns it away to short fine leg

Rakep lets go of a stumping chance, he came charging down , and missed this flighted ball completely, it went between his legs as he looked to work it through midwicket, tough take for Rakep, Ervine was in no shape to get back in time if he had collected cleanly
now he gets a single through midwicket
tries the bouncer, it sits up meekly, he goes for a languid, almost casual pull, the ball takes the top edge and flies backward of square leg and rolls in to the boundary
clipped away off the pads wide of deep midwicket
goes a touch fuller and across the stumps, better line, he gets front foot out and pushes to mid off
strays in line again, worked off the pads to fine leg easily
he is still a bit tentative in getting fully forward, maybe the uncertain bounce is causing it, takes a step out and pushes to point
swivels for a weak pull shot, ends up swinging a bit early, and takes the short ball on the body
gets half-forward to a delivery turning across him, opens the face at the last moment and gets it past short third man who dives in vain
lovely little reverse paddle, from leg stump too, slightly fuller and turning in, he reaches out and wristily turns it comfortably past short third man, too fine for him to bother chasing it
turns it from way outside leg stump, he plays it out on the leg side
pushed out towards midwicket
comes forward to defend, gets it towards short fine leg and they take the single
dabs it away towards short third man, some bounce on it but he manages it in the end
whoa, whoops, where did that come from, it went some four feet down the leg side, after being looped up in the air
pushed away to short extra cover
eased down to long off for a single
comes down the track, takes this on the half volley and collects the run to long on
one more single down the ground, they are a dime a dozen, long off this time
gets this one to turn in and bounce from outside off stump, Elton does well to keep it down
goes for the sweep to one turning down leg stump, gets a top edge that has short fine leg interested for a moment, but not after it flies way over his head
well, he sprays the first one a foot down the leg side from a length, Kenya need to pull things back here, they are leaking runs
short, and wide again, this time outside off stump, slashed away to third  man
shot! Elton plants front foot across and down the track, picks this fuller one from outside off stump, and swings it high and mighty over long off, Zimbabwe are getting a real move-on
now the single to fine leg off the pads
front foot across the stumps, and a clip off the pads to midwicket
not much possible with this one, on the stumps and he pushes it back to the bowler, Nehemiah is a touch lazy in getting down and concedes a run down the ground
fuller outside off stump, and he pings long off with the front foot drive
strays down the leg side, again, this time Rakep gets pads in the way, and stops it
one more fluffed stumping, Rakep holds his head down in disappointment, Tikolo had deceived Elton in the flight, and it turned down the leg side, but Rakep could not collect
clipped away through midwicket for the single
driven forcefully off the front foot, sweeper cover has it, er, covered
pushed out in to the off side off the front foot
turned off the pads to short fine leg
gets this one off the front foot past extra cover
bowls the cutter around leg stump, he tries to turn it fine but can't beat the fielder
fuller delivery around leg stump, he adjusts to push it past extra cover
waits on the back foot for this shortish one to come on, swivels and pulls it over midwicket
again stays in the crease to push out a length ball on the off side
clipped neatly off the toes, but right to midwicket
and Ervine falls over outside the crease as he comes out to one that is bowled down the leg side, could have been a stumping chance, but extremely tough take
more leg side stuff, this time Ervine flicks it to fine leg and jogs through for the run
turns and bounces too much way outside off, Obuya misses the take
played out with the turn to midwicket
takes this one on the half volley, and goes through with the drive, mid off helps by running across and diving over the ball
looking to have a swing at everything now, this one goes down to deep square leg
shortens the length as he sees him come out, and he hits it away to extra cover
that is big! Ervine gets one in the slot, goes down on the knee and slog-sweeps it from outside off way over deep midwicket, and many rows back
rolls away off the pads fine to the keeper on the leg side as he targets the fuller length
good adjustment from Elton, it was the slow short delivery, he had lined up for the big pull, and adjusted pretty neatly to pull it along the ground wide of deep midwicket
goes for the fuller length again, squeezed out near the wickets
goes for the yorker, sprays it down the pads, and it rolls away fine on the leg side
what does the bowler do? what can he do? Ervine goes across the stumps, and turns a length ball from way outside off stump, paddles it to the fine leg boundary, that will be his 50
101.1 kph slower one, he waits for it, and picks the gap perfectly past extra cover with the drive, Kenya can't stop the runs
looks to swing this one over square leg, but it was not short enough, and rolls away on the off side off the body
and he walks outside the off stump, takes this length ball from a couple of pace down the track, and lifts it over midwicket
shuffles again, but this one is not full enough and he plays it out on the leg side
Ervine is getting way outside off stump repeatedly, and hurting Kenya, he brings out the lap shot now, scrambles in the end but manages to pick it wide of short fine leg from outside off stump
even the top edges are not finding the fielders, he went for the forcing pull, got the steepling edge that fell well short of fine leg
Elton is finding some for here, pulls a shortish one ferociously but finds the man at deep midwicket
bounces high outside off stump, he almost jumped in the air to reach it, but could not connect
does not have to do too much stretching for this one, gentle length ball a foot outside off, and he gets front leg out of the way, and swings it over wide long off
played out in to the leg side
gets a low full toss, goes down on the knee to swing it, but takes it on the pads
takes the almost-yorker length ball and does well to squeeze it wide of mid off, but Mishra does even better to rush to his left and dive to save the boundary
and now he pulls off a well-timed catch, Elton swung this one with power down the ground, but Mishra timed his leap at the precise moment to take the ball that was sailing over his head
Ervine continues to find the middle of the bat, creams a length ball off the front foot to sweeper cover
Obuya takes the ball, and goes up for the catch, but it was off the thigh pad as Lamb missed the waft across the line
lovely drive from Lamb, got forward to ease this fuller one in to the gap between sweeper cover and long off, both of whom gave up early
tries the short delivery this time, and gets away with it as it bounces high over the batsman

that is right off the toe end of the bat, that is why it weakly looped in the air and fell short of short fine leg, else the way he had swung the blade, it would have been picked up behind the deep square leg boundary
he is gone now, went for a forceful punch to a length ball and chopped it on to the stumps
swung with a loud crack to the man at deep midwicket, if only you could get more runs for middling it off the bat, that would have been a six, it was absolutely belted
almost shopped on to the stumps, but he escapes with a single fine down the leg side
fires in the bouncer, it comes slowly off the pitch, he goes for the pull, but it is too high for him, not called a wide

slower one, really slower one, he was half-way through with the pull, stopped, and then helped it fine on it's way to fine leg where Rakep flung himself to his right and stopped the ball inches from the ropes
Lamb connects and gets more than enough on this length ball to send it screaming over the wide long off boundary
Rakep is in business again, this one is worked away off the pads wide of fine leg
this is some acceleration from Zimbabwe, now it is Utseya, almost sweeps this shortish delivery in Moin Khan fashion, and it carries flat and over the deep square leg ropes
another one, almost carries over the ropes, skips down the track, adjusts to one on the leg stump, and lifts it on one leg and past deep midwicket, brings up the 300 too
Kenya have nowhere to hide now, Utseya has charged down and blasted this one down the ground and over the bowler's head

that is some of the finest pieces of work on a cricket field, he had bent the knee, looking to go over fine leg with the scoop, but realised it was too much outside off for that, and just twirled the wrists to turn the face of the bat, and got the ball neatly past the keeper
tries to do the delicate adjustment again fine on the off side, but misses
takes a step down the track, and has a swipe, thick edge down to third man, and Zimbabwe have surged and swelled like a river in monsoon, and Kenya's hopes have been flooded over

inn2.comm: and right away, a back of a length ball takes of sharply, he fends at it and is fortunate to get an edge over slip
closer to off stump this time, and fuller too, left alone
squares him up a bit with one that straightens around off stump, pushed away in front of cover
another good delivery, at 134.5 kph moves away from the forward prod. and beats him outside off
and he gets rewards for some lovely bowling, fuller and angled in on the stumps, he was caught by surprise, and took it on the pads, he is a goner,says the umpire
he is getting so much bounce from outside off stump, another one takes off from back of a length around off, left alone this time
pushed through on the leg stump, pushes out and takes it on the pads
pushed past Price, and they take on mid off with the throw, and make it in the end
pushed through again, this time on middle, punched down the track
tossed up this time, gets him to push out, they think of the single, but extra cover gets to it quickly
pushed out on the leg side off the back foot
tight as always, worked away off the back foot to square leg
rides the bounce on a back of a length ball to push it out to cover
Utseya gives up the chase from short fine leg, it was worked away off the pads fine past the keeper
comes forward to a length ball that angles in and leaves him outside off, leaves him poking awkwardly in the end
pushed out to point this time off the back foot, Mpofu is all over Kenya at the moment
Taibu does well to take a lifter that takes off from a short length and bounces over the batsman who looks to pull initially but backs off in the end
punched off the back foot to cover, a bit more intent this time
tries the surprise full delivery on the stumps, but he manages to stab it back down the track
comes down the track and pushes this one to long on
pushed through quicker, he comes out and smothers it

direct hit from short third man, it was guided in that direction and they were attempting the quick single, they go to the third umpire, and he is caught just short of the crease, good work from the fielder, got quickly to the ball and fired in the throw without wasting any time, Collins has to walk back
almost gets through, it is fired in and hurries on low, just jams his bat on it in the end
payed out to midwicket carefully
goes straight in on leg stump, whipped away to deep midwicket
gets an inside edge onto boot and it rolls away on the off side as he looks to block off the back foot
flicked off the pads, timed neatly, races away to the deep midwicket boundary
looks to flick fine down the leg side, gets it off the pads, Taibu goes flying to his left to take it
gets behind the line of a length ball on middle stump, and defends
bowls it one the pads, Tikolo flicks again, gets it off the middle of the bat again, and another boundary to deep midwicket
goes for the yorker, dug out in to the leg side
gets it away off the back foot, it was homing in on off stump quickly, but he rocked back and cut it in front of cover
looking to play from deep in the crease, another one hurries in, jabbed away on the off side
on the leg stump and turned to square leg
short fine leg and square leg in the circle and he fires another one on the pads, talk about bowling to your field
defended off the front foot, this one is bowled a lot slower
still slower, tossed up as well, Price going through the entire range, smothered off the front foot
goes down the leg side from short of a length, he tries to whip it fine but misses
rides the bounce on one outside off to cut it away in the air but past point, third man tidies up
comes back in from short of a length, he hurriedly defends
the fuller delivery that he tries every now and then, squeezed out towards mid on, and they take him on with the run, and complete it comfortably
pushed away off the back foot off a thick inside edge towards midwicket
stabbed away towards point off the back foot, Mpofu continues with the short of length stuff
goes past the outside edge of Tikolo, moved away a shade from back of a length outside off and he had a poke at it
comes forward and gets an inside edge to short fine leg
they take on Sibanda with a nudge towards point, and make it safely

that looks to be the end of Tikolo for one final time, he went back to one that hurried on, missed the waft and was struck on the pads in front of leg stump, umpire Dharmasena raised the finger right away, Tikolo goes for the review, but to no avail, that is taking out leg stump, in a lovely gesture, all the Zimbabwe players rush to shake hands with Tikolo as he walks back, the grand old man of Kenyan cricket gets a standing ovation from the sparse Kolkata crowd who know their cricket only too well, the Kenyan dressing room applauds as one, the Zimbabwe players continue clapping in unison right till the very end, the end of the Kenyan legend
defended solidly off the front foot
another solid forward defensive push from Tanmay
and again, right forward to defend this one, Price is right on target, ball after ball
blocked off the back foot, gets on the toes and defends down the track
walks a step or two down the track, and has a swing at this one, gets it past mid on cleanly
pushed away in front of point and they go through for the single
gets a leading edge as he looks to turn a length ball on the leg side, ball rolls away to cover
comes forward with a big backlift but in the end blocks a length ball on off stump
jags back in sharply to strike him on the pads as he is caught in the crease, looked too high
comes forward to defend a flat delivery
looks to go for the sweep to one on leg stump, gets it fine enough on the leg side
played out to midwicket off the back foot
for once Price goes short and a shade wide, enough for him to rock on the back foot and cut it in front of point
played languidly out to short extra cover
flighted around middle and leg, gets bat and pad together as he blocks
and is swept right away behind square leg for a boundary from middle stump
turned away in front of midwicket, it was flighted generously

Mishra has thrown it away, he is such a fine player of spin, but that won't please him one bit, with fine leg up, he goes for the sweep, and gets a meek top edge that settles in to that man's hands, Utseya is in business right away
defended off the front foot on the off side
played out to midwicket off the back foot
blocked off the front foot down the track
swept away to square leg
strikes him on the pads, looked to be going down leg
driven towards extra cover off the front foot

Price keeps firing them in, there is no getting away, this one strikes him on the pads in front of the stumps again as he pushes forward, pad first and then bat it seems, umpire Dharmasena thought so, and gave him out, they go for the review, and it only confirms the umpire's decision
flighted ball, defended off the front foot
bowls this one slowly through the air, he gets forward to defend
fuller ball, played back down the track
blocked off the front foot down the track
Utseya goes up in appeal, another one strikes the pads, lots of turn, that is why there was doubt in the umpire's mind
played back down the track
gets this one past the bowler, and past mid on too, just a push but it was timed well
leading edge this time, Utseya is getting them to stay very low and turn sharply, the ball rolls away to point
lovely variation from Price, he turns this one after flighting it slowly, the edge does not carry to slip
almost another one, played away towards square leg, Taibu went after it and fired in a wild throw else Odoyo was gone
gets him to jab at one that rushed on quickly
now one bowled slowly, giving him the working over, blocked off the front foot
he pushes this one on off stump, and he manages to smother it
Price flights it again, but down the leg side, and Rakep sweeps it fine backward of square leg, that was a freebie, well, he is not pricey with gifts every now and then
goes deep in the crease to push a turning delivery back to the bowler
charges out and takes it on the full, pushes it down the ground to long on
defended off the front foot calmly on off stump
driven with the turn this time to long on along the ground
stands in the crease and looks to go for the cut, too close for the shot and is beaten, it was quicker too
eased down the ground to long on for a single
takes it on the pads as he pushes forward
shuffles across the stumps to work it away to deep midwicket
played with the turn down to long on
turning in, whipped away off the pads wide of midwicket
gets a thick inside edge that goes to short fine leg as he looks to whip it away
eased away to extra cover off the front foot
defends off the front foot in to the off side
skips down the track and drives down the track, but Utseya gets a hand to it
fuller outside off stump, and he stays in the crease to smash it past cover for a boundary
punched off the back foot to the bowler
goes forward and drives with the turn to long on
tosses it up generously, he drives it to long off this time
looped up gently on off stump, defended into the leg side
shot! Lamb pushed it up too full on off stump this time, and Patel eased into a classy drive that beat Taylor at mid-off. A Good-looking stroke, high left elbow
pushed down to long-on for one
pushed through quicker, and Odoyo is beaten by some sharp spin off the surface ... he's struck on the pad but outside off
half an appeal from Taibu this time as the ball spins sharply again, but that's turning too much
solidly defended to end the over
eased down the ground to long off for a single
shuffles across to work a turning ball to deep square leg
works this fuller one towards square leg and they take the single by the time midwicket gets to the ball
tossed up slowly in the air, turned to midwicket
driven hard down the track, but straight to the bowler
Utseya completes another tight over with yet another dot ball
flighted outside off stump, driven down the track
pushed in to the off side off the front foot
swept backward of square leg from off stump
goes back to whip a turning ball through square leg

strikes him on the pads right in front of middle as he goes back and misses the waft across the line, that looked dead if there is no inside edge, it lodged between the two pads, umpire Dharmasena thinks there is some wood on that, Zimbabwe want the review, that is hitting middle of middle, there does not seem to be any bat, and that is the end of Thomas Odoyo
and another one struck in front, again the umpire shakes his head, this one was much quicker and fuller, turned in sharply as he pushed outside the line, could have gone down leg with the turn
turned off the pads to short fine leg
pushed down the track off the front foot
slapped through extra cover off the front foot
tossed up and he takes it on the half volley to ping long on for the single
takes it from some way outside off stump and paddles it past short fine leg, who gives chase and pulls it back
flighted from round the stumps, smothered down the track
lunges forward to one that turns in, and gets an inside edge towards midwicket
turns in sharply from outside off, strikes him on the pads as it bounces high
worked away in front of square leg, and there is some confusion before they decided not to go for the run
looks to break free with a huge backlift but in the end plays this one out to midwicket
pushed away in front of covers off the front foot
looks to turn this one from outside off stump fine down the leg side, is hit on the pads
down the track, to the pitch, and bosh! lifts it straight down the ground, and in to the boundary
defended off the front foot down the track
goes for the cut now, but hits it to point
goes through backward point, got some bad bounce, he went for the cut and it bounced just before the fielder
pushed away in front of point who dives to his right to field
looks to swings it out of the park, gets it down to long off for the single
goes down on a knee and merrily swings a fuller one to deep square leg
floated up on off stump and turning away, guided with an open face towards point
looks to sweep a very full delivery, gets it in front of square leg
plonks this one in front of covers and off they go

this one didn't get off the ground much, he went for the cut but seemed to underedge it through to the keeper, Taibu thought so as he took it, umpire Dharmasena did not think there was any bat, there was a loud sound as it passed the bat, they go for the review, there does not seem to be any deflection, can't give those against the batsman
tossed up on leg stump, pushed in to the leg side
defended off the front foot close to silly point
hits him on the pads with some sharp turn, too much to have the umpire in doubt
punched off the back foot past the bowler to long off. wonder why they still have him on the boundary
goes for the reverse sweep, but gets a top edge that falls short of extra cover
now Rakep teaches short fine leg, goes for the sweep and the top edge eludes that man all the way to the boundary

falls finally on his last attempt, goes for the slog sweep, seen three forms of the shot in three deliveries, this one is hit the farthest of the three, but not beyond the man at deep midwicket who takes a well-judged catch on the boundary
front leg goes out of the way, and he has a huge heave at a very full delivery, and it flies over wide long off, very powerfully hit
Ongondo departs second ball, tossed up on leg stump, and turns to strike him pad first as he pushes forward, right away umpire Dharmasena raises the finger, Zimbabwe need two more
floated up outside off stump, draws him forward and turns away to beat him
fuller on leg stump, and worked away through midwicket
pushed out in front of cover this time
waits in the crease and guides this one past short third man
another top-edge, but this one falls safely, he went for the big slog sweep from way outside off stump but it fell short of deep midwicket
tossed up outside off for the drive, he gets an inside edge back to the bowler
defended off the front foot in front of square leg
punched off the back foot, but extra cover dives and stops the ball
gets the sweep from the middle of the bat this time, and in the gap  between deep midwicket and deep square leg

dropped Ervine puts down a mile-high skier, Nehemiah threw the bat at it and it flew in the air, Ervine ran in from long on, got to the ball, it  popped out of the hands, got to it again, but parried it away, tried once more before it came down on the ground
played away on the off side
the reverse sweep, he is enjoying it in the middle, gets another one off the middle, and it goes through the man in the circle
chopped close to the stumps off the back foot
backs away for the cut, but the ball turns away from him and he is beaten
slapped off the back foot wide of long off
pushed through on the leg stump, defended off the front foot very carefully
turns and bounces sharply and he almost plays on
pushes away for another single this time
pushed away off the front foot towards extra cover
played out to midwicket
pushed away to silly point off the front foot
whipped away wristily to midwicket
cuts with the turn to extra cover and gets back before the throw comes in

goes for the reverse sweep now to one that then strikes him in front of the stumps, umpire Dharmasena shakes his head after a long look, he is right again, that pitched outside leg, Dharmasena has a smile on his face as he shakes his head again after they go for the review
turns across him and keeps very low, he goes for the pull and plays all over the ball
superb delivery that pitches middles on a length, and turns across the forward prod outside off stump
shortish and turning away, he goes back and cuts hard, extra cover gets across and fires in the throw
comes down the track and drives down the ground to long off
very full ball on the stumps, tails in, and goes very fine down the leg side off an inside edge
driven off the front foot to mid off for a single
ends up as a high full toss and is flicked away to fine leg, there is some reverse swing for Mpfou
another one almost chopped on, but the inside edge flies to fine leg past a diving Taibu
defended solidly off the front foot from a length outside off stump
comes forward and pushes a length ball away to midwicket
looks to launch this one over extra cover, but pulls out of the shot, this one didn't get up at all, wise decision
Elton's direct hit sends Otieno on his way, they attempted a quick single towards covers but Elton fired in the throw at the striker's end to catch him inches short of the crease
tossed up, draws him forward and it turns away outside off stump, excitement from slip and gully as Taibu collects
guided to gully with an open face with the turn
fired in quicker, defended off the front foot
the wrong 'un tossed up high, but miles outside off stump, bounces sharply but Taibu takes it cleanly
this one hurries straight on outside the off stump, he walks across and leaves
full delivery, bashed down the ground to long off
flighted one on middle, blocked off the front foot
turns away a fuller one to midwicket, Nehemiah is slow off the blocks but makes it in the end
tries to comes down the track, then decides to hang back and chops it to Price at backward point who lets the ball through again
and he turns this one through where forward short leg would have been
guides this one past slip who stays in his place, but Taibu goes scooting after the ball to loud cheers, and comfortably pulls it back

Cremer thinks he has his man, he backed away for the cut and it rushed on to strike him on the flap, in front of middle, but umpire Dharmasena is unmoved, that was taking out middle, maybe he thought it was bat first
played out in front of cover off the front foot
Ngoche comes down the track, and launches this one against the turn and over long on, crowd love it
pushed off the front foot on the off side
surprised by the bounce on this one, plays it out on the leg side in the end
comes forward and blocks off the front foot
Nehemiah is loving this stint, lines up for the reverse sweep and gets it past backward point
gets another boundary, comes down the track, winds up and has a go, the ball flies over cover and rolls in to the boundary
another reverse sweep, this time it goes in the air, but Price at short third man takes ages to get to this right and is still miles from the ball when it comes down
bashed off the front foot, almost carries to the bowler
defended off the front foot as it turns in from outside off
gets him to come forward with a flighted delivery and it turns in past the outside edge
goes back and pulls in the air and down to long on
they all go up in appeal as he strikes him on the pads with one that slides on, looked a touch high, well, well, it would have taken out leg stump, they did not go for the review
played out in to the off side
takes off from outside off stump, left alone
blocked off the front foot, bat and pad close together
that will be the end of it all, Ngoche came down the track and looked to launch this one over deep midwicket, but only got it as far as Mpofu on the boundary
